d 'PRCOINT': module to perform Perron and Rodriguez (2016) residual-based tests for cointegration under endogeneity and serial correlation 
d
d  prcoint computes the residuals-based tests of Perron and
d Rodriguez (2016) for cointegration under endogeneity and serial
d correlation. The deterministic components are removed from each
d series by local-to-unity GLS detrending before the cointegrating
d regression is estimated. Seven statistics are reported based on
d the autoregressive spectral density estimator of the long-run
d variance with BIC lag selection. The tests remain valid under
d endogenous I(1) regressors and serially correlated errors. Three
d deterministic cases are covered (constant; constant and trend;
d constant with trending regressors). 
d
d KW: unit root tests
d KW: cointegration
d KW: Perron
d KW: Rodriguez
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260719
d
d Author: Ozan Eruygur,  Ankara Haci Bayram Veli University
d Support: email eruygur@@gmail.com
d
